enhanced_by.reason: Both methods modify the internal state of the Attribute object by updating its key or value.
The constructor initializes the key and value, which can be used to set up the initial state for testing setValue.
The html method generates the HTML representation of the attribute, which can be used to verify the effect of setValue on the attribute's HTML output.
The equals method can be used to compare the Attribute object before and after calling setValue to ensure the value has been correctly updated.
